results.name: The largest number m such that sigma(m) = A007368(n), where A007368(n) = the smallest k such that sigma(x) = k has exactly n solutions.
comment: A184393(n) is the sequence of the smallest such numbers. Row n of A201915 gives all n values satisfying sigma(x) = A007368(n).
link: Donovan Johnson, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: For n = 5, sequence of defined numbers m_5: 30, 46, 51, 55, 71; a(5) = 71.
results.author: _Jaroslav Krizek_, Jan 12 2011
